b'Late night Taco Bell visits are a college staple, and for two friends like Bri and Ben, it became a place of refuge. They loved being the first to try new menu items when they were released as a way to blow off steam from their stressful classes. Talking over tacos soon evolved into something more, and their friendship blossomed into romance. In all of their travels and life changes, they could always find a Taco Bell to just sit and talk. Their wedding day was no different. :two_hearts:\nCredit: @beck.bee'

b'John and Jeannine were both born and raised in St. Louis, Missouri, and met working at their local Taco Bell. Sparks flew between the two of them, and their relationship grew into something much more than coworkers. 25 years later, it was only fitting that they celebrated their wedding anniversary by renewing their vows at the Las Vegas Taco Bell Cantina surrounded by family and friends. Although they love Crunchy and Soft Tacos, their Cinnabon Delight cake was the star of the show. :birthday_cake:\nCredit: https://www.aimleephotography.com'

b'Imagine if your first date ever was over Crunchy Tacos and Baja Blast. This was a reality for Jordan back in 2018, when she and her friend Cole (who she had been crushing on for months) were headed to Taco Bell for what she thought was just a normal meal together. Little did Jordan know it was a date, as she had never been on one! They stayed for five hours talking until the restaurant closed, when Jordan started to realize they were becoming more than friends. A year later they came back to where it all began and took anniversary pictures together. They love going back to the restaurant that started it all. :red_heart_selector:\nCredit: @heartofflesh'
